about.label: About
about.content:
About ASEAN PATENTSCOPE


The ASEAN PATENTSCOPE project was initiated by the ASEAN Patent Examination Co-operation (ASPEC) Task Force in 2012 and endorsed by ASEAN Working Group on IP Cooperation (AWGIPC) in 2015 after the adoption of the WIPO Publish technical platform to automate the data extraction, data dissemination and searching among all ASEAN IP offices. Indonesia has contributed extensively towards leading the project and hosting the regional patent database


ASEAN PATENTSCOPE provides a centralized regional online platform for dissemination of patent information for all 10 ASEAN countries and facilitates the ASEAN IP Offices to share patent data with international global IP systems, such as WIPO CASE for patent examiners, WIPO PatentScope and IP5 Global Dossier Systems for public users. The users in the region have access to patent collections from all ASEAN member states, many of them for the first time, and can access a comprehensive and complex technological information resource in the region. The ASEAN PATENTSCOPE portal has several notable features to assist users, including bibliographic data search, view of published patent dossier information, capturing search results in a customizable report and translations into national languages.


The system that was developed in the framework of this project is modern and effective and should make a substantial contribution to the increasing access to the ASEAN regional patent information by the users of ASEAN IP systems and by the international IP community.


The system is provided by the World Intellectual Property Organization (WIPO) through its program of technical assistance to national and regional Industrial Property (IP) Offices. Parts of the system development are provided through the support of the Japan Funds-in-Trust for Industrial Property (for more information, see
http://www.wipo.int/cooperation/en/funds_in_trust/japan_fitip_aspac/index.html)


For more information on WIPO’s technical assistance programs, please see
http://www.wipo.int/global_ip/en/activities/technicalassistance/
